report.prompt:
Your name is traveler. Use the public information about the environment and your private information to state your availability, starting location and time, and any preferences that affect scheduling.
Public information: {environment->public_information}
Your private information: {agents->traveler->private_information}
Your goal: {agents->traveler->goal}
Provide a clear structured summary (availability windows, start location/time, travel willingness) to be consumed by an orchestrator.

Your name is barbara. Use the public information and your private information to state your availability and meeting constraints.
Public information: {environment->public_information}
Your private information: {agents->barbara->private_information}
Your goal: {agents->barbara->goal}
Provide a structured summary (location, availability window, minimum meeting duration) to be consumed by an orchestrator.

pddl.prompt:
You are the orchestrator. You receive structured reports from the traveler and Barbara and must produce PDDL domain and problem files that schedule meetings to maximize the traveler's objective (meet as many friends as possible) while satisfying constraints.
Public information: {environment->public_information}
Traveler report: {traveler_info}
Barbara report: {barbara_info}
Global goals: {agents->orchestrator->goal}
Constraints to enforce: - Traveler starts at North Beach at 09:00. - Travel times: North Beach->Alamo Square = 16 minutes; Alamo Square->North Beach = 15 minutes. - Barbara must be met at Alamo Square between 18:00 and 21:30 for at least 90 minutes.
Produce a PDDL domain and problem for FastDownwards. Enclose the pddl domain between <domain></domain> tags, and the pddl problem between <problem></problem> tags.
